Three types of ExposedLocator can be selected.
1. Locator within rendering: Transform embedded in prefab renderings.
2. Common locator: a predefined locator that always exists for each character, etc. (e.g. observation point, hit location)
When multiple targets exist, a given target can be specified using its number (e.g. multiple corresponding skills)
3. A character's own custom locator: a special locator for skill renderings of the triggering character. Can be displayed and selected from the BattleUnitPointContainer LocatorList.

How to preview during rendering creation:
The SkillDirectionView component has a SerializeField for previews, and by setting the triggering character and target character there, you can set and perform a preview.

For more configuration details, refer to each track within the ExposedLocator Demo in a scene's ExposedLocatorSampleDirection.
